Consider the following class:

```csharp
public class FillUp
{
  public DateTime FillDateTime { get; set; }
  public double OdometerReading { get; set; }
  public double Litres { get; set; }
}
```

Write a method that accepts a list of objects of that type. These represent fill-ups at the petrol station. The ```OdometerReading``` is the car's odomenter reading at the time of the fill-up, and ```Litres``` is the total number of litres that went into the vehicle at that time.

Your method should return a list of objects of the following type:

```csharp
public class MonthlyFillUpSummary
{
  public string MonthSlashYear { get; set; } //For example, "01/2017" for January 2017
  public int NumberOfFillups { get; set; }
  public double TotalLitres { get; set; }
  public double AverageLitres { get; set; }
  public double DistanceDriven { get; set; }
}
```

This list should contain one item per month of fill-ups in the input data, and each item should contain a summary of the total number of fill-ups, the total litres filled, the average litres filled, and the total distance driven, for that month.

Hint: the total distance driven will be the difference between the odometer reading of the last fill-up for the month, and the odometer reading of the first fill-up for the month.
